content.description:
AKA:

Crowbar

Pretty good quality rock with still a touch of loose stuff here and there. Great views and cool rock up toward the top.
content.location: Walk along the base of the wall until you see an obvious ledge angling back toward the parking area. Standing on the ledge, this is the farthest left bolted line.
Start on far left on the prominent belay ledge, Furthest route left, fourth route from left.

content.description:
Pumpy, consistent, full of crack features and trends to the right. Small roof to pull halfway. Called

Tantenbesuch

in another book.

Another featured climb with some loose rock, some very interesting limestone pockets and huecos, and a wandering path.

Called Aunts In Your Plans

in another guide.
content.location: Second climb uphill of the belay ledge.

content.description: Climb up a tiny left facing dihedral and pull up to a small ledge. Here the fun starts with great edging past several bolts. A series of large holds provide relief near the top.
content.location: Look for large flake at the start with a single bolt on a left face followed by many up a face.

content.description:
Fun climbing up some edges and pockets over a small roof leads to the crux moves in the dihedral. Don't duck off to the left or you'll end up on the 5.9. Called

Antsy Assembly Line

in another book.
content.location: Just a few feet downhill from Gerry Rig in a left facing dihedral.

content.description: Interesting climbing through roofs and features with sometimes suspect rock.
content.location: Hike along base of cliff up from belay ledge.  This is the first route you get to.

climbs.name: Gerry Rig
climbs.fa: Robin Groschup, Franziska Garrett, and James Garrett, 2011

content.description: This route looks a little blank at the bottom but climbs great edges all the way to the top. The glue in bolts are difficult to see in spots but help identify which route you're on. When in doubt head straight up. The route is almost dead straight.
content.location: This is the farthest right route on Blob's Your Aunt/Tokey Dokey wall. Climbs through many golden bands of rock.

content.description: Nice climb with a cool roof that isn't hard if you find the good stuff
content.protection: bolts and anchors, unknown quantity (bring 10 to be safe)
content.location: Right of 101 Kicken Chicken (Aunts in Your Pants). Starts about where the uphill trail branches out onto the belay ledge.

content.description:
AKA:

Aunts in Your Pants

More cool rock. A bit more thin than Whiskey Crew (Crowbar), but good.
content.location: Just right of Whiskey Crew (Crowbar) on the same nice belay ledge.
